{"questionId":"33020502","questionHtml":"<p>Use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math> to show that if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math> is a root of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, then <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></math> is also a root.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>α</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mi>α</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>α</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp; (as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math> &nbsp; (hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>α</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1<br><br></strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN<br></strong></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></math> is also a root&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <em><strong>R1</strong></em> is dependent on the <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>α</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (seen anywhere),&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>α</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mi>α</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> and so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>α</mi></mfrac></math> is also a root&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <em><strong>R1</strong></em> is dependent on the <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33020502","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use px=xnp1x to show that if α≠0 is a root of px=0, then 1α is also a root.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}